parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic park system can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, even when the transmission is in the "Park" position, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly when the transmission is in the "Park" position
the vehicle stops suddenly while driving
the vehicle is unable to move when the transmission is in the "Park" position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential fires, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.

The malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and loss of vehicle control, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.

The failure of the dual pane window seal can cause moisture to accumulate between the panes, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially when driving a large vehicle like a motorhome.
symptoms: fogging or hazing of the window
white substance or condensation on the glass

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate attachment of wheel liners can cause them to come loose while driving, potentially striking other vehicles or pedestrians, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Wheel liners become detached while driving
unusual noise or vibration from the wheels

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The insufficient length of wheel stud bolts can prevent proper attachment of wheel liners, leading to loose or detached liners, which can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: wheel liners becoming loose or detached
unusual noise or vibration from the wheels
wheel studs or bolts appear too short.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the circuit breaker can cause the expandable room to inadvertently pop up, which can lead to unexpected changes in vehicle configuration, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The expandable room suddenly and unexpectedly deploys
the circuit breaker trips or fails
unusual noises or vibrations are heard or felt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of malfunctions, including the inadvertent deployment of the expandable room, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: unusual noises or vibrations are heard or felt
the circuit breaker trips or fails
the expandable room suddenly and unexpectedly deploys.
